fields.description:
The data for the Dashboard comes from the JAG. Based on the research that was done in [https://frontlinetechnologies.atlassian.net/browse/HCMAT-25477|https://frontlinetechnologies.atlassian.net/browse/HCMAT-25477|smart-link] , the JAG does not currently load in the Language Definitions for Entitlements.

We will need to do the following:

* Modify the DAL_LoadEntitlementTypeBase sproc to bring back the Language Definitions (stored in the {{ReferenceData_Description}} table.
* Modify the JAG/DAL to map the ReferenceData_Description entries to a new Collection on the EntitlementTypeBaseObject
** There could be multiple language definitions per entitlement type, but there should only be one definition for a given entitlement type and language.
* Modify the endpoint on the JAG that the Dashboard hits to take a Language parameter
** update the logic to take the user’s language into account 
*** the description field that we return should be the language definition for the user’s language
*** If there is no language definition for the user’s language, then we should just use the entitlement type description

I think this most closely matches ‘JAG OPTION 2’ from the research ticket (HCMAT-25477)

Could require updates to the Event Analyzer.



Language Definitions do not Display on Campus User Dashboard
Recreated in test org 15992
1 Login as FA@Email.com/TEST12345
2 Go to the dashboard and change the date to 11/13/2019.
3 Absence 390089076 will show Personal Day as the absence reason when it should show the Language Definition of PTO. If you switch over to the daily report it will show PTO.

* Please see Zendesk Support tab for further comments and attachments.

Need a research task to see if the JAG is even loading this data.  Might be able to point on Thursday.

fields.description:
Ran a query to find situations where a worker's org_ID does not match the org_ID of an institution they are assigned to. This is causing issues pulling up and editing these users in their source orgs. It's a similar problem to the mismatched skills.

I ran:
select
w.org_id as 'Worker Org ID',
o.appl_ID as 'Worker Appl_ID',
i.org_id as 'Inst Org ID',
o2.appl_ID as 'Inst Appl_ID',
i.inst_id,
wi.inst_id,
wi.WI_ID,
--i.inst_name,
--i.inst_active,
--i.inst_deleted,
w.work_id,
w.work_LastName,
w.work_firstname

from worker w with (nolock)
left join Worker_Institutions wi with (nolock) on wi.WORK_ID = w.WORK_ID
left join Institution i with (nolock) on wi.INST_ID = i.INST_ID
left join organization o (nolock) on w.org_ID = o.org_ID
left join organization o2 (nolock) on i.org_ID = o2.org_ID
where
w.org_id != i.org_id
and (o.appl_id in (5,10,20) or o2.appl_ID in (5,10,20))
and w.WORK_Deleted = 0
and wi.WI_Deleted = 0

To find situations in KES, ESS, and IWS. What I need is to have these WI_ID's marked as deleted, AND each work_ID assigned to the top level institution of the org they are in. It's one more step in the process than cleaning up skills because users need to be assigned to at least one institution.

ESS is currently going through a process to get onto the MOMUAP, so this work is in relation to that. As it turns out, if a user is listed as "Active" in Time and Attendance, they have that option when logging into Frontline. The problem is, ESS has a number of districts that have TA turned off, but the users are still listed as active in those districts. 

So, what I need is this: A list of all of the orgs in APPL_ID 10, whether or not the district is active in TA, and whether or not there are any users that are undeleted and active in TA specifically. Also, a list of any users that are undeleted and active in TA while in a district that does not have TA turned on.

The actions from here are going to be two fold, but in other JIRAS - they want to review the list and turn off TA for districts where it's not being used, and they also want to review it and make inactive any user in a district where TA is currently not on. 

Normally a request like this is something we can pull, but I cannot find were "active in TA" is held in the DB. If you can include whatever query you are running, that would help me in the future.
